        "description": "The Europaplus API is a JavaScript library designed to interact with the Europaplus radio service in Russia. It allows developers to access various functionalities such as retrieving schedules and other data associated with the radio service.",
        "servers": [
          {
            "description": "Europaplus Radio Service",
            "url": "https://www.europaplus.ru"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Europaplus API",
        "version": "1.0.0",
        "tagline": "Unofficial access to Europa Plus, a major Russian commercial radio station, including schedule and search data",
        "homepage": "https://www.europaplus.ru",
        "docs_url": "https://freepublicapis.com/europaplus-api",
        "about_md": "[Europa Plus](https://www.europaplus.ru) (Европа Плюс) is one of the largest commercial radio networks in Russia, broadcasting popular music, charts, and on-air shows such as Бригада У and ЕвроХит Топ 40. The website at `www.europaplus.ru` exposes a handful of JSON endpoints that power its own pages.\n\nThis SDK wraps the public, unauthenticated endpoints reachable on the radio station's site. Typical use cases include:\n\n- Looking up scheduled programmes and on-air content\n- Issuing search hints against the station's catalogue (e.g. `GET /api/search/hint?query=...`)\n\nThis is an unofficial integration. The endpoints are undocumented and may change without notice, and CORS is not enabled, so calls generally need to be made from a server-side environment.",
        "entity_desc": {
          "schedule": "Programme schedule / on-air listings for the Europa Plus radio station, exposed under the site's `/api/` namespace."
